oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Formation of vinyl ether derivatives in the reaction of tributyltin hydride with cluster supported fischer carbene complexes: structural characterisation of [(CO)6Fe2Te2{μ-PhC=CC(OEt)}W(CO)5]
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: MATHUR, PRADEEP
GHOSH, SUNDARGOPAL
UMBARKAR, SHUBHANGI B
WALAWALKAR, MRINALINI G
PURANIK, VEDAVATI G
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: iron
tellurium
cluster
x-ray diffraction
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Treatment of the complex [(CO)6Fe2EE′{μ-C(Ph)=C–C(OEt)=M(CO)5}], (1: E=S, E′=Se; M=Cr; 2: E=S, E′=Se; M=W; 3: E=E′=Te; M=Cr and 4: E=E′=Te; M=W), with excess Bu3SnH in hexane at 0°C produces enol ether derivatives: (CO)6Fe2{μ-EC(Ph)(H)-C(E′)=C(H)(OEt)} (E/Z-5: E=S, E′=Se and E/Z-6: E=E′=Te). All the compounds have been characterised by IR and 1H-, 13C- or 77Se-NMR spectroscopy. The structure of [(CO)6Fe2Te2{μ-(Ph)C=CC(OEt)}W(CO)5] has been established crystallographically.
